              Browse Table.bm (local listings) →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); margin-top: var(--space-6);">Tipping</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">
          Bermuda follows roughly the same tipping convention as the US: 15–20% on restaurant
          bills where service is not included. Check the bill — some restaurants add a service
          charge automatically (typically 15–17%), in which case no additional tip is expected
          unless service was exceptional. The practice varies by restaurant.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); margin-top: var(--space-6);">Alcohol</h3>
        <p>
          Rum is Bermuda's signature spirit — Gosling's Black Seal is the local brand. The
          Dark 'n' Stormy (Black Seal rum, ginger beer, lime) is Gosling's trademarked cocktail
          and available everywhere. The Rum Swizzle — rum, falernum, citrus, bitters — is the
          other Bermuda cocktail worth having at least once. You can try both at the Swizzle Inn
          in Bailey's Bay, which lends the drink its name.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted);">
